==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reissners membrane
<hw>Reiss"ner's mem"brane</hw> <pr>(r?s"n?rz m?m"br?n)</pr>. <ety>[Named
from <person>E. <etsep>Reissner</etsep></person>, A German
anatomist.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The thin membrane which
separates the canal of the cochlea from the vestibular scala in the
internal ear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reissuable</ent>⟦br⟧
